"'''And the Band Played On: The Band's Tale'''" is a short story by [[John Gregory Betancourt]] focusing on the [[Max Rebo Band/Legends|Max Rebo Band]] picking the wrong time, place, and employer for a gig. It appears in the anthology ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', published by [[Bantam Spectra]] [[December]] [[1995]].

==Plot summary==
[[Evar Orbus and His Galactic Jizz-Wailers]] came to [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] expecting to perform in [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]]. However, on their way to the [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]], they are attacked by [[Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes/Legends|Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes]]. [[Evar Orbus/Legends|Orbus]] is [[Death/Legends|killed]] in the fight allowing [[Max Rebo/Legends|Max Rebo]] to take over the band. After the cantina job busted, the new [[Max Rebo Band/Legends|Max Rebo Band]] is desperate for a job. 

Max, [[Sy Snootles/Legends|Sy Snootles]], and [[Droopy McCool/Legends|Droopy McCool]] secure a gig at [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]]. The voraciously single-minded Max agrees to the band being paid in [[Foodstuff/Legends|food]]. Sy agrees to [[Spy/Legends|spy]] on any conspirators plotting against [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]]. The band rides aboard the [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]] during the failed execution of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and escapes the blast that consumes the floating pleasure craft. Max and Sy decide to carry on as the [[Max Rebo Duo]], while Droopy wanders into the [[Desert/Legends|desert]] to find others of his kind.

==Continuity==
Because this story was published before the release of the [[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Special Edition]] of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']] ([[1997]]), the expanded [[Max Rebo Band/Legends|Max Rebo Band]] was absent from the tale, and the musical ensemble was merely a trio.<ref name="TERC" />

